-- Xylem Names GE Executive as Managing Director for India Water
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-10-07T14:25:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-07/xylem-names-ge-executive-as-managing-director-for-india-water.html
Xylem Inc. (XYL) , the water technology
company spun off by ITT Corp., today announced the appointment
of  General Electric Co. (GE)  executive H. Balasubramaniam as managing
director for India.  Balasubramaniam was business director of GE’s locomotive
projects and formerly served as chief executive officer of GE
Water Process and Technologies, South Asia. Xylem’s works in
India, the second-most populous nation, include power,
industrial, irrigation, water and wastewater-treatment projects.  “His success in growing GE’s water business in India fit
perfectly with our need to develop further in this important
growth market,” said Steve Loranger, CEO and president of Xylem.  ‘‘Bala’’ replaces Sam Yamdagni, who’s leaving the company,
White Plains, New York-based Xylem said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
